article.headline: Texas St. 86, Jacksonville St. 83
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Brent Benson scored 21 points and Ty Gough had 9 points and 11 rebounds despite battling foul trouble to lead Texas State to an 86-83 victory over Jacksonville State in the consolation game of the 100 Club Classic Saturday. Benson and Ryan White each hit a basket to break a 77-77 tie for a 4-point lead with 1:07 to play. Will Ginn then hit a basket and drew a foul, sinking the free throw to cut the lead to 1 with 54 seconds to play. After Texas State (3-1) regained a 3-point lead, Ginn missed a 3 and Chris Agwumaro, who had 12 points, hit a dunk on the other end. Ginn and freshman J.R. Weathers led the Gamecocks (1-3) with 13 points each and Nick Murphy added 10.
